Error: Error: "Failed To Allocate A Minecraft Server". This Error Occurs On A Pterodactyl Panel When Trying To Create Or Start A Minecraft Server, And It Typically Happens Because There'S Not Enough Memory Allocated To The Server.

Solution: Step 1: Log in to your Pterodactyl panel and go to the server console.

Step 2: In the console, type the command "free -m" (without quotes) to check the available memory on your system.

